1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,570
Go on, he said.

2
00:00:02,320 --> 00:00:06,130
Well, there are two kinds of action that seem to fit your case.

3
00:00:06,320 --> 00:00:11,010
First, start this afternoon to move those sales figures upward.

4
00:00:11,041 --> 00:00:12,371
We've got to face it.

5
00:00:12,481 --> 00:00:14,931
There's a reason your sales are slipping.

6
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:15,971
Find it.

7
00:00:16,320 --> 00:00:20,611
Maybe you need a special sale to clear out your slow-moving merchandise,

8
00:00:20,611 --> 00:00:23,411
so you'll be in a position to buy some fresh stock.

9
00:00:23,601 --> 00:00:26,611
Perhaps you can rearrange your display counters.

10
00:00:26,720 --> 00:00:29,731
Maybe your salespeople need more enthusiasm.

11
00:00:30,080 --> 00:00:35,010
I can't pinpoint what will turn your sales volume upward, but something will.

12
00:00:35,121 --> 00:00:39,731
And it would probably be wise to talk privately with your merchandise manager.

13
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:45,651
He may be on the verge of putting you out, but when you talk it over with him and ask his advice,

14
00:00:45,681 --> 00:00:48,851
he'll certainly give you more time to work things out.

15
00:00:49,121 --> 00:00:57,890
It's too expensive for the store to replace you as long as top management feels there's a chance you'll find a solution." I went on.

16
00:00:58,320 --> 00:01:01,171
Then get your assistant buyers on the ball.

17
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:03,250
Quit acting like a drowning man.

18
00:01:03,361 --> 00:01:06,450
Let people around you know that you're still alive.

19
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:09,491
Courage was again in his eyes.

20
00:01:09,601 --> 00:01:14,051
Then he asked, You said there are two kinds of action I should take.

21
00:01:14,080 --> 00:01:15,411
What's the second?

22
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:20,291
The second type of action, which you might say is an insurance policy,

23
00:01:20,320 --> 00:01:27,171
is to let two or three of your closest business friends in the trade know you might consider an offer from another store,

24
00:01:27,280 --> 00:01:31,171
assuming, of course, it is substantially better than your present job.

25
00:01:31,681 --> 00:01:39,250
I don't believe your job will be insecure after you take some affirmative action to get those sales figures on the rise.

26
00:01:39,520 --> 00:01:42,690
But just in case, it's good to have an offer or two.

27
00:01:42,880 --> 00:01:50,771
Remember, it's ten times easier for a man with a job to get another job than it is for someone unemployed to connect.

28
00:01:51,520 --> 00:01:55,250
Two days ago, this once-troubled executive called me.

29
00:01:55,760 --> 00:01:58,130
After our talk, I buckled down.

30
00:01:58,241 --> 00:02:03,091
I made a number of changes, but the most basic one was with my salespeople.

31
00:02:03,280 --> 00:02:07,890
I used to hold sales meetings once a week, but now I'm holding one every morning.

32
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:10,851
I've got those people really enthusiastic.

33
00:02:11,121 --> 00:02:15,330
I guess once they saw some life in me, they were ready to push harder, too.

34
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:18,611
They were just waiting for me to start things moving again.

35
00:02:19,041 --> 00:02:21,250
things sure are working out okay.

36
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:27,731
Last week my sales were well ahead of a year ago and much better than the store's average." Oh,

37
00:02:27,921 --> 00:02:32,291
by the way," he continued, I want to tell you some other good news.

38
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:35,331
I got two job offers since we talked.

39
00:02:35,601 --> 00:02:41,651
Naturally I'm glad, but I've turned them both down since everything is looking good here again.

40
00:02:42,321 --> 00:02:47,891
When we face tough problems, we stay mired in the mud until we take action.

41
00:02:48,161 --> 00:02:52,690
Hope is a start, but hope needs action to win victories.

